Apple Clang 17+ build fix: rename static satpos in sdr_pvt_afs.c

Bundled with the LSIS-AFS Test Vectors v0.4.0 release.  Apple Clang 17
(shipped with macOS Command Line Tools 15.x / Xcode 17 onwards)
upgraded "static declaration of 'satpos' follows non-static
declaration" from a warning to a hard error, breaking PocketSDR-AFS's
libsdr.a build because src/sdr_pvt_afs.c declares a file-static
satpos() whose name shadows RTKLIB's exported int satpos(...) in
lib/RTKLIB/src/rtklib.h (different signatures).

This patch renames the file-local helper to satpos_afs and updates its
single in-file call site.  No semantic change.  Independent of the
test-vector cross-decode functionality, but required for clean builds
on contemporary macOS.

Pinned upstream SHA: 5b23809f30d68518b7fad7a564fd0fac57cc497d.

License: BSD-2-Clause (matches the upstream PocketSDR-AFS license).

---
diff --git a/src/sdr_pvt_afs.c b/src/sdr_pvt_afs.c
--- a/src/sdr_pvt_afs.c
+++ b/src/sdr_pvt_afs.c
@@ -89,7 +89,7 @@ void xyz2llh(const double *xyz, double *llh)
 
     return;
 }
-static void satpos(ephem_t eph, gpstime_t g, double* pos, double* vel, double* clk)
+static void satpos_afs(ephem_t eph, gpstime_t g, double* pos, double* vel, double* clk)
 {
     double tk;
     double mk;
@@ -215,7 +215,7 @@ static double computeRange(ephem_t eph, gpstime_t t_rcv, double xyz[], double dt
     }
 
     // SV position at time of the pseudorange observation.
-    satpos(eph, g, pos, vel, clk);
+    satpos_afs(eph, g, pos, vel, clk);
 
     // Receiver to satellite vector and light-time.
     subVect(los, pos, xyz);
